way to do safety in taxis,

00:55:31.300 --> 00:55:35.150
better way to rate the experience
and regulate the safety

00:55:35.150 --> 00:55:40.150
of the experience in
hotels and quasi hotels.

00:55:40.830 --> 00:55:42.810
And is a challenge to the old model

00:55:42.810 --> 00:55:44.710
of an inspector with a license.

00:55:44.710 --> 00:55:46.880
And that's the model that we have now.

00:55:46.880 --> 00:55:51.019
And so we're seeing a battle
between those two forms

00:55:51.019 --> 00:55:53.160
and it'll be really interesting to see

00:55:53.160 --> 00:55:54.350
how that how that plays out.

00:55:54.350 --> 00:55:58.660
I'm sure that the sharing economy
institutions have shown us

00:55:58.660 --> 00:56:01.480
new ways to do some things
that we haven't known

00:56:01.480 --> 00:56:03.600
how to do nearly as well before.

00:56:03.600 --> 00:56:06.150
And I'm also sure that
they're in some other ways

00:56:06.150 --> 00:56:07.940
skirting some rules that
we're gonna have to try

00:56:07.940 --> 00:56:09.770
to figure out how to reimpose.

00:56:09.770 --> 00:56:12.440
- And then in the end it's really gonna be

00:56:12.440 --> 00:56:14.810
about interest group behavior,

00:56:14.810 --> 00:56:17.831
who's gonna get mobilized to either be

00:56:17.831 --> 00:56:19.330
for or against this.

00:56:19.330 --> 00:56:24.330
It's also about the lawyers
who can help us understand

00:56:25.550 --> 00:56:29.630
how this fits into what
you call the institutions

00:56:29.630 --> 00:56:33.260
and the sentiments that
define American nationalism.

00:56:33.260 --> 00:56:34.150
- Yeah, and it's a good thing.

00:56:34.150 --> 00:56:37.350
I mean, I think you know,
one of the things that might,

00:56:37.350 --> 00:56:40.010
