00:57:11.880 --> 00:57:15.383
we're gonna see the law
have to come to terms

00:57:15.383 --> 00:57:18.680
with that kind of thing.

00:57:18.680 --> 00:57:22.520
- Well, with their set of
problems like that before us,

00:57:22.520 --> 00:57:25.850
and having walked you
through some of the problems

00:57:25.850 --> 00:57:27.036
that you dealt with,

00:57:27.036 --> 00:57:28.960
my last question will be this,

00:57:28.960 --> 00:57:32.810
How would you advise students
to prepare for the future,

00:57:32.810 --> 00:57:35.640
especially, if they wanna go into law?

00:57:35.640 --> 00:57:37.800
And should they become historians too?

00:57:37.800 --> 00:57:39.320
- Well, they absolutely
should become historians.

00:57:39.320 --> 00:57:41.090
One of the great virtues
are being a historian,

00:57:41.090 --> 00:57:42.190
well, two virtues, you know,

00:57:42.190 --> 00:57:45.150
one is you haven't ruled
out any methodology.

00:57:45.150 --> 00:57:47.020
You can do economic history,

00:57:47.020 --> 00:57:48.673
you can do the history of sociology,

00:57:48.673 --> 00:57:51.010
you can do the history of
English literature, right.

00:57:51.010 --> 00:57:53.610
So history is a way of not
ruling out a methodology,

00:57:53.610 --> 00:57:56.820
it's in some ways it's kind of
a cheat as a result of that,

00:57:56.820 --> 00:57:58.366
but the real reason to study history is

00:57:58.366 --> 00:58:01.000
that otherwise you're like an amnesiac

00:58:01.000 --> 00:58:02.920
walking through time and space.

00:58:02.920 --> 00:58:04.220
And so having some sense

00:58:04.220 --> 00:58:07.710
of the kinds of features
of the human experience

00:58:07.710 --> 00:58:09.074
allows you to make sense of the meaning

00:58:09.074 --> 00:58:12.940
of the kinds of things we do
today, and hopefully tomorrow.

